President Obama has proclaimed November 2015 as National Alzheimer's Disease Awareness Month. He acknowledges the challenges faced by people with Alzheimer's and their loved ones, and emphasizes the need to support them. The Federal Government is leading the funding of Alzheimer's research and supporting a variety of research initiatives. The President also highlights the importance of supporting family caregivers who dedicate themselves to caring for those with Alzheimer's. He calls upon the people of the United States to learn more about Alzheimer's disease and show support for individuals living with the disease and their caregivers.